    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-01-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Hale</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 29.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-01-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 23, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir :</hi> Your despatch of December 27, No. 72, has been
                    received and is approved. You will make known to the government of the Pacha
                    that the President of the United States has been highly gratified by the
                    considerate and friendly disposition which the Egyptian government has
                    manifested in permitting and aiding the arrest and delivery of John H. Surratt,
                    who is charged as an accomplice in the assassination of the late President
                    Abraham Lincoln.</p>
                <p>As a token of the satisfaction which I am thus authorized to communicate, the
                    President has instructed me to procure a portrait of the deceased President, to
                    be presented in the name of the United States to his highness the Pacha. This
                    instruction will be promptly executed.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Hale,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
